cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper investigates the performance of object recognition systems as the amount of training data grows, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on discriminatively trained templates, which is a popular approach in object recognition and falls under the category of supervised learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of regularization and outliers, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
